title: VOTE: L1 Player of the Month
text:
Vote NOW for your PFA Fans' Player of the Month in League One Last Updated: 06/03/17 4:55pm Vote NOW for your PFA Fans' Player of the Month in League One Vote now for your Sky Bet League One PFA Fans' Player of the Month for February. 
Our expert panel has produced a stellar shortlist of contenders, including Sheffield United striker Billy Sharp, Millwall defender Jake Cooper and Bradford City forward Charlie Wyke. 
They face fierce competition for the award from Oxford United's Conor McAleny, Southend United's Marc-Antoine Fortune and Gillingham's Josh Wright. 
The shortlist was chosen by our expert panel, which included Sky Sports pundits Paul Merson and Peter Beagrie, Mike Riley - general manager of the Professional Game Match Officials, and Malcolm Clarke - chairman of the Football Supporters' Federation. 
Remember, one voting fan in each division will win the chance to meet and present the award to each PFA Fans' Player of the Month. 
Voting will close at 7pm tonight with the winner announced at 10am on Wednesday.
